[White "Tal Variation: 4.h4 h5 5.Bd3: 7.Bd2"]
[Black "Quickstarter Guide"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 c6 2. d4 d5 3. e5 Bf5 $1 { The bishop gets out. Later White's centre can be attacked with ...c5 or ...f6. } 4. h4 h5 $1 { Preventing **g4**. Don't fall for } ( 4... e6 $2 5. g4 Be4 6. f3 Bg6 7. h5 { . } ) 5. Bd3 Bxd3 6. Qxd3 { This is a better version of the bishop exchange for White. Here they get the g5-square. } 6... Qa5+ $1 { An important move. } ( 6... e6 { is also possible, but then } 7. Bg5 { is annoying. } ) 7. Bd2 { [%csl Ra5] } 7... Qa6 { [%cal Ga6d3] One of the key ideas of **6...Qa5+**. Black would love to get the queens off. This is fine for Black because the ending is never a problem. } * 

