1. e4 c6 2. d4 d5 3. e5 Bf5 $1 { The bishop gets out. Later White's centre can be attacked with ...c5 or ...f6. } 4. Nc3 { Positionally speaking, the knight is misplaced here, blocking the c-pawn. There is cunning idea behind } ( 4. Nc3 { , though. } ) 4... e6 5. g4 { The Shirov variation. White goes all-in on sharp play, trying to get the initiative with very aggressive moves. Black's structure is very firm and not so easy to overrun and modern engines confirm that this is a risky strategy for White. } 5... Bg6 6. Nge2 { [%cal Gh2h4] [%cal Ge2f4] [%csl Rg6] White wants to continue with **h4**. It is necessary to prepare this with } ( 6. Nge2 { , as the premature } ) ( 6. h4 { is met with } 6... h5 $1 { , when closing the kingside with } 7. g5 { gives Black a free hand on the other side: } 7... c5 { and Black already has good play. } ) 6... c5 $1 { [%csl Rd4] [%cal Gb8c6] Black strives for active counterplay. } 7. h4 h5 $1 { A pawn sacrifice that slows White's play down. Black's play is in general based on very direct counterplay. Some of the hardcore lines are quite complicated, but the basic logic is simple: We create our own chances by fighting fire with fire! } 8. Nf4 Bh7 $1 { Sacrificing the h-pawn. } 9. Nxh5 cxd4 $1 { [%cal Gb8c6] It is important to destroy White's centre. Black gets promising play in all lines. Play typically can go in two directions. } 10. Qxd4 { This looks very active, but the queen becomes a target and Black takes over. } 10... Nc6 { [%csl Rd4] [%csl Re5] } 11. Bb5 { Pinning the knight. White keeps playing active moves. } 11... Ne7 $1 { [%cal Ge7c6] [%cal Ga7a6] Making sure that Black can take back on c6 with a knight. The plan is to play ...a6 next and force White to give the bishop. } 12. Bh6 { If you have never seen this spectacular move before, it might shock you! The bishop can't be taken because of } 12... Rg8 { [%cal Gg8g7] [%csl Gg7] A cool response, just protecting g7. You can find a nice victory for Black in the Model Games (See "Model Games" variation from the PGN). } ( 12... gxh6 13. Nf6# { mate, and White attacks the g7-pawn. } ) * 

