$1 { Now the position gets wild! This piece sacrifice is more or less forced, because } ( 10. exf6 gxf6 11. Be3 e5 { is just a winning position for Black with a strong centre and an extra pawn. } ) 10... fxg5 { The safest is to accept the piece. } 11. Qb3 { [%csl Rb7] Hitting b7 is not fast enough for White. } 11... Nd7 12. Qxb7 { [%csl Ra8] } 12... Rb8 13. Qxc6 Rh6 $1 { [%cal Gh6c6] Active defence is the key. } 14. Qxd5 g4 15. Ng5 e6 { [%cal Gf8c5] [%cal Gg8e7] Black was winning in Vujovic-Karthik, 2024. } * 

