[Result "*"]

1. e4 c6 2. d4 d5 3. e5 Bf5 4. Nc3 { Positionally speaking, the knight is misplaced here, blocking the c-pawn. There is cunning idea behind } ( 4. Nc3 { , though. } ) 4... e6 5. g4 { The Shirov variation. White goes all-in on sharp play, trying to get the initiative with very aggressive moves. Black's structure is very firm and not so easy to overrun and modern engines confirm that this is a risky strategy for White. } 5... Bg6 6. Nge2 { [%cal Gh2h4] [%cal Ge2f4] [%csl Rg6] White wants to continue with **h4**. It is necessary to prepare this with } ( 6. Nge2 { , as the premature } ) ( 6. h4 { is met with } 6... h5 $1 { , when closing the kingside with } 7. g5 { gives Black a free hand on the other side: } 7... c5 { and Black already has good play. } ) 6... c5 { The typical break. } 7. h4 h5 $1 8. Nf4 Bh7 { Sacrificing the h-pawn. } ( 8... cxd4 9. Nxg6 fxg6 { is a playable alternative. } ) 9. g5 { [%csl Gf5] Closing the kingside is anti-positional and it gives Black the f5-square. } 9... cxd4 10. Nb5 Be4 $1 { [%cal Yf2f3] [%cal Ye4f5] [%csl Rh1] We want to go to f5, but first we force White to weaken the position with f3. } 11. f3 Bf5 12. Nxd4 { I once met } ( 12. Bd3 { . After } 12... Bxd3 13. Qxd3 g6 { I was much better, Sulskis-Schandorff, Denmark 2010. } ) 12... Ne7 { [%cal Ge7f5] [%csl Gf5] Protecting the bishop. } 13. Nxf5 Nxf5 14. Bd3 Qc7 $1 { [%cal Gc7e5] [%csl Re5] A nice intermediate move. Suddenly e5 hangs with check. } 15. Bxf5 { This leads to some forced play that ends badly for White. } 15... Qxe5+ { [%cal Ge5f5] The point. Black takes the pawn with check. } 16. Qe2 Qxf5 17. Qb5+ { This way White regains the pawn. The price is high, though. } 17... Nd7 18. Qxb7 Rb8 19. Qc6 { This has all been seen. } 19... Bc5 { [%cal Ge8g8] [%cal Gb8b4] This move just wins. White's kingside is too open. A sample line goes } 20. Nd3 O-O $1 21. Nxc5 Qxf3 22. Rf1 Qg3+ 23. Rf2 Ne5 24. Qa6 Ng4 25. Qe2 Rb4 26. Qf3 Qg1+ 27. Ke2 Rc4 28. Nb3 Qxf2+ 29. Qxf2 Rxc2+ 30. Bd2 Nxf2 31. Kxf2 Rxb2 { followed by ...Rc8 with a winning ending. } * 

