1. e4 c6 2. d4 d5 3. e5 Bf5 4. g4 $5 { [%csl Rf5] White has had some success with this brutal move recently. Compared to the more sophisticated Shirov variation with } ( 4. Nc3 e6 5. g4 { , this direct attack on the bishop looks more weakening than helpful. There are certain dangers - for both sides, you could add - so it is important to know what to do. } ) 4... Be4 $1 { [%csl Rh1] Forcing White to weaken the kingside with f3. In case of the immediate Black can consider } ( 4... Bg6 { White can play in many ways, for example } 5. Ne2 e6 6. Nf4 { . There is no reason to enter this. } ) ( 4... Bd7 { , which is a solid, but rather passive move. The idea is to play ...e6 next with a French type of position. I prefer to keep more tension, though. } ) 5. f3 Bg6 6. e6 { A positional pawn sacrifice. This is probably the best move for White in the position. } 6... Qd6 { [%cal Gd6e6] [%csl Re6] I prefer to leave the pawn on **e6**. } ( 6... fxe6 7. h4 { gives White compensation. } ) 7. exf7+ Bxf7 { Here White has tried several moves. } 8. Nc3 { Probably the most critical try. } ( 8. f4 { Controlling the e5-square, but giving e4 away. } 8... Nf6 9. Nc3 g6 { Intending ...Bg7. } 10. Bh3 { This has scored well for White, but Black is doing fine after } 10... c5 11. Nf3 cxd4 12. Nxd4 Bg7 { followed by ...O-O and ...Nc6 . } ) 8... Nd7 { [%cal Ge7e5] Preparing the ...e5 break. The immediate } ( 8... e5 9. dxe5 Qxe5+ 10. Nge2 { followed by Bf4 is good for White. } ) 9. f4 { White needs to stop it. } 9... h5 { [%csl Gg4] Disturbing White's pawn formation. Black has even tried } ( 9... g5 { with the idea } 10. fxg5 e5 { with compensation. Also possible is 9. f4 9...Ngf6 . } ) 10. g5 e6 11. Nf3 Ne7 { [%cal Ge7f5] [%csl Gf5] An interesting position. White controls the e5-square, but Black has a nice outpost on f5. The light-squared bishops play a major part in the coming phase. } 12. Bd3 ( 12. Bh3 Bg6 $1 { followed by ...Bf5 is fine for Black. } ) 12... h4 $1 { [%cal Gf7h5] Played by the World's strongest player. } 13. O-O Bh5 { [%cal Ge8c8] [%cal Ge7f5] [%cal Gg7g6] Black has activated the bishop and has decent counterplay. The position is complicated, but balanced. Tari-Carlsen, World Cup 2023 continued } 14. Qe1 g6 15. Ne5 Bg7 16. Bd2 Nf5 { and Black was slightly better. } * 

