1. e4 c6 2. d4 d5 3. e5 Bf5 4. h3 e6 { [%cal Gc6c5] Well, g4 is not a big threat, so just play natural moves. } 5. g4 { Otherwise h3 doesn't make much sense. } 5... Bg6 { The simplest. } ( 5... Be4 { is met by } 6. Nf3 { which is, of course, also good for Black, but let's keep it simple. } ) 6. h4 h5 $1 { [%csl Rg4] We know this by heart. } 7. g5 c5 { [%cal Gb8c6] [%csl Gf5] Black is much better. White's adventure on the kingside has mainly resulted in some weak light squares. } * 

