1. e4 c6 2. d4 d5 3. e5 Bf5 4. h4 h5 5. Bd3 Bxd3 6. Qxd3 { This is a very popular line for White. Black's next move is important. } 6... Qa5+ $1 { Black gives this check at once, before White can get the bishop to g5. } 7. b4 { A cunning gambit that the engines support. } 7... Qa6 { A clever practical decision. Taking the pawn is possible, but White gets good long-term compensation: } ( 7... Qxb4+ 8. Nd2 e6 9. Rb1 Qe7 { . That being said, Black is solid and a pawn is a pawn! } ) 8. e6 { Another surprising pawn sacrifice. Keeping the queens on with } ( 8. Qb3 { is possible, but Black is fine after } 8... e6 { . } ) 8... Qxd3 9. cxd3 ( 9. exf7+ Kxf7 { basically just helps Black to develop. } ) 9... fxe6 10. Nd2 Nh6 11. Ndf3 Nf5 12. Ne2 { [%cal Ge2f4] [%csl Ge5] [%csl Gf4] [%csl Gg5] The knight is on the way to f4. White controls e5, f4 and g5 which looks quite scary for Black. In fact there are no problems, as the strong German GM shows. } 12... g6 13. Nf4 a5 $1 { Going for active counterplay instead of trying to hang onto the extra material. } 14. Nxe6 { Or } ( 14. Nxg6 Rg8 { and Black's rook is strong. } ) 14... Kd7 15. Nxf8+ { Also } ( 15. Nc5+ Kc8 { is fine for Black. } ) 15... Rxf8 16. bxa5 Rxa5 { Objectively speaking, the position is probably balanced, but Black has a strong knight on f5 and some long-term chances based on the superior pawn structure. } 17. O-O { Better is } ( 17. a4 { . } ) 17... Ra4 $1 { [%cal Ga4d4] [%cal Ga4a2] Attacking d4. } 18. Ne5+ { Going for some direct play. Or } ( 18. Be3 Kc7 19. Rfe1 Nd7 { and Black is ready to continue with ...Rfa8, with strong pressure. } ) 18... Kc8 19. Nxg6 Rg8 20. Nf4 Nxd4 { However, White didn't calculate this very precisely. White's position turns out to be really bad! } 21. f3 ( 21. g3 Nd7 22. Nxh5 Nf3+ 23. Kh1 Nxh4 { can lead to a fun mate after } 24. gxh4 $2 Rxh4# { . } ) 21... Nb3 { Winning an exchange. Maybe it was even better just to develop with } ( 21... Nd7 { . } ) 22. axb3 Rxa1 23. Nxh5 Na6 24. d4 Nb4 ( 24... c5 $1 { immediately is also strong too. } ) 25. Nf4 Nc2 26. Ne2 Rb1 27. h5 Rxb3 28. Kf2 ( 28. g4 { is pretty unclear. } ) 28... c5 29. Nf4 Rh8 30. dxc5 e5 $1 31. Nxd5 Rxh5 32. Nf6 Rh8 33. g4 Nd4 34. Kg2 Rc3 35. Ne4 Rc2+ 36. Bd2 Nb3 37. Rf2 Nxc5 38. Bc3 Rxf2+ 39. Nxf2 Re8 40. Kg3 Kd7 { The time control has been reached. Black is completely winning. } 41. g5 Ke6 42. f4 exf4+ 43. Kg4 Rc8 44. Bd4 f3 45. Kxf3 Kf5 46. Be3 b5 47. Bd2 Rd8 48. Bc3 Ne6 49. g6 Kxg6 50. Ke4 Nc5+ 51. Ke3 Kf5 52. Bb4 Ne6 53. Nd3 Rg8 54. Bd6 Rh8 55. Bb4 Rh3+ 56. Kd2 Rf3 57. Ne1 Rh3 58. Nd3 Nf4 59. Nc5 Rh2+ 0-1 

